Description: Plastic box (with yellow label '64') with transparent lid containing fragments of papyrus and an old card with note in 'Fragment from of Sams impositions'. A label by Stephen Quirke reads 'Three coptic fragments ... Kept in Keeper's Room to 1992 Jan'. The fragments inside are unmounted and unglazed.
Curator's comments: Previously unregistered material stored in Papyrus Store.
